                      "page": null,
                      "version": null,
                      "material_number": null
                    },
                    "date": 1990
                  }
                }
              },
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "The cross section of monitor reaction were defined by",
                "interpolation of the evaluated values of the reference",
                "from \"Physik Daten - Physics Data, Evaluation of Cross",
                "Sections for 14 Important Neutron-Dosimetry Reactions.",
                "Fachinformationszentrum Karlsruhe, Gesellschaft fur",
                "wissenschaftlich-technische Information mbH, Federal",
                "Republic of Germany, No. 13-5 (1990)\"."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "D-T"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The tritium-titanium (T-Ti) target used in the",
                "generator was 2.18 mg/cm2 thick. The effective source",
                "neutron energy at irradiation position was determined",
                "by the (n, 2n) reaction ratio between Nb and Zr."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-T",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The total uncertainty are mainly include the",
                "counting statistics, the detector efficiency, the",
                "self-absorbability of gamma-rays, the standard cross",
                "section, the weight of samples and the coincidence sum",
                "effect of cascade gamma-rays."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "During irradiation, the neutron flux was monitored by",
                "accompanying alpha particles so that the corrections",
                "could be made for small variations in the yield. The",
                "self-absorption of the sample at a given gamma-energy,",
                "the coincidence sum effect of cascade gamma-rays in",
                "the investigated nuclide and in the counting geometry",
                "were taken into account in data analysis, respectively."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "STATUS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "status": [
                  "TABLE"
                ],
                "subentry_number": null,
                "author": null,
                "reference": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " All measured reactions data and monitor",
                "reaction data are taken from Table2 at page 644 in",
                "J,NIM/B,269,2011."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "According to the contents of measurement, in Table1 1",
                "the reaction production nuclei decay information for",
                "61Ni(n, p) isn't 61mCo. It should be 61Co, and there",
                "are not exist isomeric state for 61Co."
              ]
            }
          ],
